                  <summary>Conclusion of a report of a case tried before M. Rutilius Lupus, praefect in 114-7 C.E. The litgants were Damarion, apparently a freedman, and his patron Heraclides. (Grenfell &amp; Hunt)</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Text is on one side only, 13 lines written generally with the fibers on an upward slant.  Bottom and right margins are visible.  Text mentions Egypt., specifically Egyptian law.</note>
